<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 08 at 12:58AM MDT until June 08 at 1:30AM MDT by NWS Pueblo</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 130 AM MDT
FOR NORTHEASTERN OTERO...WESTERN KIOWA...EAST CENTRAL CROWLEY AND
NORTHWESTERN BENT COUNTIES...
At 1258 AM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 7 miles north of
Cheraw, or 16 miles north of La Junta, moving southeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Two inch hail and 60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Arlington and Blue Lake.
THUNDERSTORM DAMAGE THREAT...CONSIDERABLE
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...2.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
